The Governir-elect of Niger state, Hon. Umar Mohammed Bago has appointed the former Director General of the Security and Exchange Commission (SEC) Mallam Sulaiman Ndanusa to head a 62-man transition council. The Transition Council also has two Co-chairmen, one of them being the deputy Governor-elect and former state NLC chairman, Comrade Yakubu Garba while the other is the former Minister of Commerce, Mustapha Bello. Also named is the former Commissioner for Agriculture and former SSG in the immediate past administration of Dr. Mu’azu Babangida Aliyu, Professor Mohammed Kuta Yahaya is also a member of the transition council expected to work hand-in-hand with 21-man Secretariat. According to the list said to have been drafted personally by Bago himself, the Vice chancellor of the Federal University of Technology (FUT), Minna Professor Adamu Kuta and another Professor from the same University Bashir Ibrahim Tachi are to serve as members of the Council. The transition Council set up by Bago also included 11 women among them a retired Commissioner of Police Rabi Umar, Mrs Asmau Gambo, Mrs. Mabel Ndagi and Mrs. Maryam Yunus Paiko, and a renown hotelier cum businessman of Igbo extraction, Mr. George Dike Also another separate dociment at the disposal of to our correspondent announced the composition of 22-man Secretariat by the Governor elect with the former Chairman of the Niger State Universal Basic Education Board (NSUBEB) Alhaji Isah Adamu is to serve as the head of the Secretariat. The Secretariat is also composed of six women; Mrs. Hauwa Dada, Halima Ahmed Haruna, Maryam Yussuf Adamu, Madina Ahmed Haruna Maimuna Haruna and Zainab Gogo Halilu .‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ It was however gathered that no date has been fixed for the inauguration of the two councils.